    "body": "Thanks for the info @zcbenz, however this comment on the [webview page](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/docs/api/web-view-tag.md#nodeintegration) is confusing. Does it mean I can use webview in my browserwindow (nodeintegration disabled) and have the webview inherit that setting automatically? I remember seeing a PR which make sure webview node integration inherits the BrowserWindow.\n\nCould you please clarify?\n\n> nodeintegration\n> \n> <webview src=\"http://www.google.com/\" nodeintegration></webview>\n> If \"on\", the guest page in webview will have node integration and can use node APIs like require and process to access low level system resources.\n> \n> Note: Node integration will always be disabled in the webview if it is disabled on the parent window.\n"
